100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 26, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing pressing global issues, including disarmament and the stability of Eastern Europe. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition intensified, with reports of increasing lawlessness and the rise of organized crime. Meanwhile, in the realm of science, a notable discovery of a new dinosaur species was announced, capturing public imagination and interest in paleontology.
